                            <comment id="14660287" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 6 Aug 2015 16:44:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It turns out that this is only really reproducible through mixed-version tests, because an &lt;tt&gt;AbstractThreadUnsafeParitition.SliceableIterator&lt;/tt&gt; has to be used with a NamesFilter, and that seems to only occur when processing legacy responses (although I could be missing something).  In any case, my dtests for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9704&quot; title=&quot;On-wire backward compatibility for 8099&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9704&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9704&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; do cover this with &lt;tt&gt;multi_in_compact_non_composite_test&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I verified that the behavior for &lt;tt&gt;ReverseRowSearcher&lt;/tt&gt; is correct, so only &lt;tt&gt;ForwardRowSearcher&lt;/tt&gt; was affected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/thobbs/cassandra/tree/CASSANDRA-10002&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Branch with changes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pending &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/thobbs/job/thobbs-CASSANDRA-10002-dtest/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pending &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/thobbs/job/thobbs-CASSANDRA-10002-testall/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;testall&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14661308" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2015 04:44:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Stefania&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stefania&quot;&gt;Stefania&lt;/a&gt; to review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14661436" author="stefania" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2015 07:24:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Code change is +1. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You may want to use parentheses consistently for these two lines although it is not required for correctness:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; start = nextIdx + (-searchResult - 1);
[...]
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; end = start + -searchResult - 1;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14662156" author="benedict" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2015 17:58:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s worth pointing out this code will be removed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9932&quot; title=&quot;Make all partitions btree backed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9932&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9932&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14662304" author="thobbs" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2015 19:21:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed with the fixed paren as &lt;tt&gt;e5e29104436fbccb9fb202c3305765ffde6f16b8&lt;/tt&gt; in 3.0 and merged to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s worth pointing out this code will be removed [...]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the heads-up.  Since it&apos;s a simple and obvious fix, I went ahead and committed to ensure the fix happens either way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
